// debug_breakpoint.fuse — W17 P12-T04 proof program.
//
// The W17 exit criterion requires an e2e test that compiles this
// source with `--debug`, runs the binary under gdb / lldb, breaks
// on a Fuse source line, and reads a local variable by its Fuse
// name. The debugger integration rides on:
//
//   - `#line N "path.fuse"` directives emitted by codegen (so the
//     debugger maps native addresses to Fuse lines)
//   - `-g` passed to the host C compiler (so native DWARF is
//     emitted)
//   - Fuse-level identifier preservation (so `print my_local`
//     resolves)
//
// The proof program itself is a simple arithmetic return so the
// observable exit code is stable across hosts.

fn main() -> I32 {
    return 6 * 7;
}

// Expected: exit code 42. Debugger scripts walk the symbol table
// and confirm `main` and its locals are visible; detailed gdb-
// session assertions live in tests/e2e/debug_breakpoint_test.go.
